gomodel:SYNGO_5155  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 7: \"Subcellular localization of Neurodap1 (PJA2) protein by immunoelectron microscopy. Neurodap1-immunoreactivity exists at the postsynaptic density regions of axosomatic synapses (arrows in A and B). Axospinous synapses are negative for Neurodap1 (arrowhead). Punctate Neurodaplimmunoreactivity is present on the cytoplasmic face of ER of neurons (A, C). The immunoreactivity is also seen around the vesicles and sacs of the trans-side of Golgi apparatus (D).\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Adult male Sprague Dawley rats (6-8 week old) were used.\"\n\nResult section: \"The purified antibody against the GST-Neurodapl fusion protein, thus obtained, reacted specifically with the bacterial recombinant GST-Neurodapl protein (Fig. 5D). The specificity of the antibody against Neurodapl was confirmed.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5155" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

